casebody.data:
(September 19, 1960)

Nolan, P. J., Beldoek, Ughetta, ICleinfeld and Christ, JJ., concur.

Anthony Molinaro, an Infant, et al., Respondents, v. City of New York, Defendant-Appellant and Third-Party Plaintiff-Appellant. Consolidated Edison Company of New York, Inc., Third-Party Defendant-Respondent.

Motion by respondents Molinaro to dismiss appeal denied on condition that appellant argues or submits the appeal at the November 1960 Term, beginning October 31, 1960, for which term the appeal is ordered to be placed on the calendar. The record and appellant’s brief must be served and filed on or before October 17, 1960.
